  "body": "# üêû Bug Report\r\n\r\nA call to `/eth/v1/validator/beacon_committee_subscriptions` appears to force-close the connection before sending the amount of data specified in `Content-length`\r\n\r\n**N.B. the same issue is seen with the endpoint `/eth/v1/validator/attestation_data`, so this could be a general problem with other similar requests.**\r\n\r\n### Has this worked before in a previous version?\r\n\r\nNo.\r\n\r\n## üî¨ Minimal Reproduction\r\n\r\n```\r\ncurl -v -H 'content-type: application/json' --data '[{\"validator_index\":\"1\",\"committee_index\":\"1\",\"committees_at_slot\":\"1\",\"slot\":\"1\",\"is_aggregator\":false}]' http://localhost:3501/eth/v1/validator/beacon_committee_subscriptions\r\n```\r\n\r\n## üî• Error\r\n\r\n<pre><code>\r\n* TCP_NODELAY set\r\n* Connected to localhost (127.0.0.1) port 3501 (#0)\r\n> POST /eth/v1/validator/beacon_committee_subscriptions HTTP/1.1\r\n> Host: localhost:3501\r\n> User-Agent: curl/7.68.0\r\n> Accept: */*\r\n> content-type: application/json\r\n> Content-Length: 105\r\n> \r\n* upload completely sent off: 105 out of 105 bytes\r\n* Mark bundle as not supporting multiuse\r\n< HTTP/1.1 200 OK\r\n< Content-Length: 2\r\n< Content-Type: application/json\r\n< Date: Fri, 03 Sep 2021 20:24:18 GMT\r\n< Vary: Origin\r\n< \r\n* transfer closed with 2 bytes remaining to read\r\n* Closing connection 0\r\ncurl: (18) transfer closed with 2 bytes remaining to read\r\n</code></pre>\r\n\r\nIt can be seen that the `content-length` header specifies that there should be 2 bytes returned, but no data is returned before the connection is closed.\r\n\r\n## üåç  Your Environment\r\n\r\nprysm 1.5.0-rc1\r\n",
